  <p>Instagram has filters. Photoshop has adjustment layers. But what if you just want to quickly convert a photo to grayscale, add a vintage look, or invert an image — without installing anything or paying for a subscription?</p>

  <p>The Image Effects &amp; Filters tool on ImageWonder gives you 12 one-click filters, all free, all browser-based.</p>

  <h2>Available Filters</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Grayscale</strong> — Converts the image to black and white using luminance weights</li>
    <li><strong>Sepia</strong> — Classic warm brownish-orange tone (adjustable intensity)</li>
    <li><strong>Invert</strong> — Reverses all colours (like a photo negative)</li>
    <li><strong>Vintage</strong> — Sepia + vignette combo for an aged photo look</li>
    <li><strong>Cool</strong> — Adds a blue tint for a cold, cinematic feel</li>
    <li><strong>Warm</strong> — Adds an orange tint for golden-hour warmth</li>
    <li><strong>Fade</strong> — Washes out the image for a faded, matte look</li>
    <li><strong>High Contrast</strong> — Pushes shadows and highlights for a dramatic B&amp;W look</li>
    <li><strong>Soft Blur</strong> — Applies a subtle blur for a dreamy effect</li>
    <li><strong>Sharpen</strong> — Enhances edges for a crisper look</li>
    <li><strong>Vignette</strong> — Darkens the edges while keeping the centre bright</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How to Apply a Filter</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Go to <a href="https://textwonder.com/imagewonder/image-effects">textwonder.com/imagewonder/image-effects</a></li>
    <li>Upload your image by dropping it or clicking to select</li>
    <li>Click any filter thumbnail — the main preview updates instantly</li>
    <li>For adjustable filters, drag the intensity slider</li>
    <li>Click <strong>Download JPG</strong> or <strong>PNG</strong></li>
  </ol>

